{"name":"Mathlib.NumberTheory.SumTwoSquares","instances":[],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.NumberTheory.Zsqrtd.QuadraticReciprocity","Mathlib.Tactic.LinearCombination"],"declarations":[{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/SumTwoSquares.lean#L216-L242","name":"Nat.eq_sq_add_sq_iff","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/SumTwoSquares.html#Nat.eq_sq_add_sq_iff","doc":"A (positive) natural number `n` is a sum of two squares if and only if the exponent of\nevery prime `q` such that `q % 4 = 3` in the prime factorization of `n` is even.\n(The assumption `0 < n` is not present, since for `n = 0`, both sides are satisfied;\nthe right hand side holds, since `padicValNat q 0 = 0` by definition.) "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/SumTwoSquares.lean#L187-L200","name":"Nat.eq_sq_add_sq_iff_eq_sq_mul","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/SumTwoSquares.html#Nat.eq_sq_add_sq_iff_eq_sq_mul","doc":"A natural number `n` is a sum of two squares if and only if `n = a^2 * b` with natural\nnumbers `a` and `b` such that `-1` is a square modulo `b`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/SumTwoSquares.lean#L179-L182","name":"ZMod.isSquare_neg_one_of_eq_sq_add_sq_of_coprime","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/SumTwoSquares.html#ZMod.isSquare_neg_one_of_eq_sq_add_sq_of_coprime","doc":"If the natural number `n` is a sum of two squares of coprime natural numbers, then\n`-1` is a square modulo `n`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/SumTwoSquares.lean#L163-L174","name":"ZMod.isSquare_neg_one_of_eq_sq_add_sq_of_isCoprime","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/SumTwoSquares.html#ZMod.isSquare_neg_one_of_eq_sq_add_sq_of_isCoprime","doc":"If the integer `n` is a sum of two squares of coprime integers,\nthen `-1` is a square modulo `n`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/SumTwoSquares.lean#L149-L158","name":"Nat.eq_sq_add_sq_of_isSquare_mod_neg_one","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/SumTwoSquares.html#Nat.eq_sq_add_sq_of_isSquare_mod_neg_one","doc":"If `-1` is a square modulo the natural number `n`, then `n` is a sum of two squares. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/SumTwoSquares.lean#L127-L140","name":"ZMod.isSquare_neg_one_iff'","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/SumTwoSquares.html#ZMod.isSquare_neg_one_iff'","doc":"If `n` is a squarefree natural number, then `-1` is a square modulo `n` if and only if\n`n` has no divisor `q` that is `≡ 3 mod 4`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/SumTwoSquares.lean#L110-L122","name":"ZMod.isSquare_neg_one_iff","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/SumTwoSquares.html#ZMod.isSquare_neg_one_iff","doc":"If `n` is a squarefree natural number, then `-1` is a square modulo `n` if and only if\n`n` is not divisible by a prime `q` such that `q % 4 = 3`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/SumTwoSquares.lean#L100-L105","name":"Nat.Prime.mod_four_ne_three_of_dvd_isSquare_neg_one","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/SumTwoSquares.html#Nat.Prime.mod_four_ne_three_of_dvd_isSquare_neg_one","doc":"If a prime `p` divides `n` such that `-1` is a square modulo `n`, then `p % 4 ≠ 3`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/SumTwoSquares.lean#L88-L96","name":"ZMod.isSquare_neg_one_mul","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/SumTwoSquares.html#ZMod.isSquare_neg_one_mul","doc":"If `-1` is a square modulo coprime natural numbers `m` and `n`, then `-1` is also\na square modulo `m*n`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/SumTwoSquares.lean#L79-L83","name":"ZMod.isSquare_neg_one_of_dvd","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/SumTwoSquares.html#ZMod.isSquare_neg_one_of_dvd","doc":"If `-1` is a square modulo `n` and `m` divides `n`, then `-1` is also a square modulo `m`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/SumTwoSquares.lean#L58-L63","name":"Nat.sq_add_sq_mul","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/SumTwoSquares.html#Nat.sq_add_sq_mul","doc":"The set of natural numbers that are sums of two squares is closed under multiplication. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/SumTwoSquares.lean#L52-L54","name":"sq_add_sq_mul","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/SumTwoSquares.html#sq_add_sq_mul","doc":"The set of sums of two squares is closed under multiplication in any commutative ring.\nSee also `sq_add_sq_mul_sq_add_sq`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/SumTwoSquares.lean#L35-L38","name":"Nat.Prime.sq_add_sq","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/SumTwoSquares.html#Nat.Prime.sq_add_sq","doc":"**Fermat's theorem on the sum of two squares**. Every prime not congruent to 3 mod 4 is the sum\nof two squares. Also known as **Fermat's Christmas theorem**. "}]}